WEBVTT

00:01.378 --> 00:03.581
Amen, and please be seated.

00:06.785 --> 00:13.535
Now, if you have a Bible, let me invite you to turn with me to Ephesians chapter two, verses eight through 10.

00:14.436 --> 00:27.794
We continue our study through this book together, and this morning we consider the role of God's grace and our faith and good works in the Christian life.

00:28.802 --> 00:35.109
Let me invite you to give attention to this very familiar passage, maybe special attention because so.

00:35.149 --> 00:40.235
From Ephesians 2, verses eight through 10, this is the word of God.

00:43.098 --> 00:47.363
For by grace you have been saved through faith.

00:48.545 --> 00:51.889
And this is not your own doing, it is the gift of God.

00:52.950 --> 00:56.594
Not a result of works so that no one can boast.

00:57.506 --> 01:10.343
For we are His workmanship, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand that we should walk in them.

01:10.383 --> 01:12.666
This is the Lord of the Lord.

01:12.726 --> 01:13.708
Let's look to Him in prayer.

01:13.748 --> 01:27.346
Our Father, we ask that You would give us life and health by this Word and by the work of the Holy Spirit to the

01:27.650 --> 01:30.275
glory of your name through Jesus Christ, we pray.

01:31.097 --> 01:31.458
Amen.

01:31.518 --> 01:43.904
The Apostle Paul is in this section where he's teaching Christians about our salvation so that we'll better understand and marvel at what God has done for us.

01:45.106 --> 01:46.429
What did God do for us?

01:46.990 --> 01:48.754
Let's review for just a moment.

01:49.474 --> 01:59.008
verses one to three, God found us spiritually dead in our trespasses and sins and disobedient and enslaved to our lusts and our passions.

02:00.029 --> 02:10.424
And we were by nature children of wrath, but God made us, Paul says verse four, but God made us spiritually alive.

02:11.105 --> 02:17.714
He redeemed us from our enslavement to sin and the penalty of it, and he rescued us from

02:17.986 --> 02:20.989
the wrath of God due to us, and he brought us to himself.

02:22.211 --> 02:23.872
He united us to Jesus.

02:25.114 --> 02:28.958
So that's what is said of Jesus can actually be said of us.

02:29.058 --> 02:33.262
In the end of chapter one, it says of Jesus that God raised him from the dead.

02:33.863 --> 02:44.495
And he ascended into heaven and it is seated at the right hand of God the Father almighty above all of their authority and all other names.

02:44.915 --> 02:47.698
And in chapter two, the apostle says,

02:47.970 --> 02:50.233
of us, of all who trust in Christ.

02:50.874 --> 02:55.561
And he does it because Christ is the head and we're the body and where the head goes, the body goes.

02:55.641 --> 03:06.638
He says, we likewise are raised and ascended and seated in the heavenly in Christ Jesus with Christ Jesus.

03:06.898 --> 03:13.869
It's hard to get your head wrapped around the implications of all of that, but you just know that he's asserting it as the truth.

03:14.770 --> 03:17.554
It is so as

03:17.634 --> 03:29.166
A bride is united to her bridegroom as a building is united to its foundational cornerstone as a body is united to its heads.

03:29.306 --> 03:35.052
So Christians are united in everything with Christ.

03:35.753 --> 03:37.274
And why did God do this?

03:37.434 --> 03:39.977
Why did God do this versus four to seven?

03:40.037 --> 03:44.722
We looked at this last time because he is rich in mercy.

03:46.050 --> 03:49.595
and because of the great love with which he loved us.

03:50.737 --> 03:59.911
And because of the immeasurable grace he has toward us and because of his kindness in Christ Jesus.

03:59.971 --> 04:06.922
So that verse seven in the coming ages, God will show or put on display.

04:06.982 --> 04:14.994
He will demonstrate to the universe publicly the immeasurable riches of his grace and kindness to us.

04:15.970 --> 04:21.698
And so the message of verses one to seven is we didn't save ourselves.

04:23.020 --> 04:31.913
We couldn't save ourselves being dead in our trespasses and sins, but God saved us.

04:33.856 --> 04:35.278
And He saved us by His grace.

04:35.318 --> 04:39.404
Now this raises questions then about, well, okay, but what about faith?

04:39.565 --> 04:42.409
And what about works, even good works.

04:42.489 --> 04:43.250
And if God

04:43.778 --> 04:50.767
sovereignly and graciously without our contribution saves us, then what about these things?

04:50.927 --> 04:52.529
I mean, are we saved without faith?

04:52.589 --> 04:53.230
Can we be?

04:53.290 --> 04:54.732
Are we saved without good works?

04:55.232 --> 04:58.376
I mean, do these things even matter in the Christian life?

04:58.616 --> 05:03.362
These are the kinds of questions that leave to mind when you say that salvation is of the Lord.

05:03.402 --> 05:06.947
And by grace is a gift.

05:08.769 --> 05:09.490
So here,

05:09.730 --> 05:15.876
In verses eight through 10, the Apostle Paul addresses these issues and let me highlight four lessons from the passage for us.

05:15.936 --> 05:18.318
I'll give them to you as we go.

05:18.358 --> 05:23.543
The first is this, God saves us and he saves us by his grace.

05:25.085 --> 05:30.110
Now, you're saying to me, I think you just said that already Ted, by way of introduction.

05:30.430 --> 05:38.738
And yes, because the Apostle Paul made just that point in verse five, he said, by grace, you have been saved.

05:39.938 --> 05:46.807
And now he repeats himself, verse eight, for by grace, you have been saved.

05:46.827 --> 05:47.488
You see that?

05:48.390 --> 05:50.332
Good teachers repeat themselves.

05:51.053 --> 05:57.843
Well, one reason being they know their students and their disciples need this kind of repetition.

05:58.443 --> 06:02.649
We know ourselves, we know our disciples, we know we're all prone to forget.

06:02.709 --> 06:09.138
We're all prone to downplay, saving grace in this case,

06:09.602 --> 06:15.370
And prone, we're tempted to pat ourselves on our back for our salvation.

06:16.831 --> 06:19.895
And the Apostle wants all the glory to go to God.

06:19.935 --> 06:21.898
It is justly do Him.

06:22.559 --> 06:26.884
He wants us to boast, not in ourselves, but to boast in the Lord.

06:26.925 --> 06:30.409
And so he emphasizes, God saves us.

06:30.489 --> 06:31.771
He saves us by His grace.

06:31.831 --> 06:32.792
What is this grace?

06:33.273 --> 06:37.298
Well, grace isn't a substance that God kind of doles out.

06:37.890 --> 06:40.253
Grace is a relational category.

06:41.234 --> 06:48.642
It's a disposition of unmerited favor in the face of our demerits.

06:50.424 --> 06:59.675
That is, it's God's favor to you when you don't deserve it and when in fact you deserve the opposite, his disfavor.

07:00.696 --> 07:06.162
So it's God giving you pardon for sin and spiritual life and a heavenly inheritance.

07:07.362 --> 07:13.271
when what you truly deserve is his condemnation and eternal death and hell.

07:14.833 --> 07:19.781
And the Apostle Paul, who's telling us this, knew a thing or two about God's grace.

07:20.642 --> 07:21.884
You remember his story.

07:22.485 --> 07:25.449
He was born a Jew of the tribe of Benjamin.

07:25.910 --> 07:33.441
He belonged to the sect of the Pharisees who were the conservative Bible teachers and moral reformers of their day.

07:34.102 --> 07:36.786
He was zealous for the law of God

07:37.410 --> 07:54.132
And he was certain he was right to oppose Jesus and to oppose Christians and to oppose the Christian church, believing as he did that Jesus was a false prophet and people were being led astray.

07:54.172 --> 07:55.935
And so what did he do?

07:56.035 --> 07:58.338
He sought to arrest and imprison Christians.

07:59.219 --> 08:04.306
He stood in the crowd of those who surrounded Stephen, stoning him to death

08:04.738 --> 08:08.744
Well, they laid their cloaks at his feet so their cloaks wouldn't get stolen.

08:11.007 --> 08:15.894
He approved as they threw rocks at Stephen and killed him.

08:15.974 --> 08:26.610
He ravaged the church, the Book of Acts says, he says of himself entering house after house and dragging off men and women and committing them to prison.

08:26.650 --> 08:32.338
He says in Acts 26 verse nine, I myself was convinced that I ought to do many things.

08:32.546 --> 08:37.371
in opposing the name of Jesus of Nazareth, and I did so in Jerusalem.

08:38.131 --> 09:02.514
I not only locked up many of the saints in prison after receiving authority from the chief priests, but when they were put to death, I cast my vote against them, and I punished them often in all the synagogues, and I tried to make them blaspheme, and in raging fury against them, I persecuted them even to foreign

09:02.786 --> 09:03.387
cities.

09:05.550 --> 09:22.693
And so it was that as he was on his way from Jerusalem to Damascus, some 140 miles or so as the crow flies a day of many, during many days, hunting Christians, that suddenly a light from heaven shone around him.

09:23.554 --> 09:29.381
And following to the ground, he heard a voice saying, Saul, Saul, why are you persecuting me?

09:29.442 --> 09:32.786
And he said, who are you, Lord?

09:33.858 --> 09:37.622
And he said, I am Jesus whom you are persecuting.

09:39.964 --> 09:44.509
What did Jesus do with a man who was killing his people?

09:46.631 --> 09:47.272
He intervened.

09:48.573 --> 10:01.586
He stopped him in his tracks and he revealed to him the truth and he had mercy on his soul and he forgave a self-righteous

10:02.306 --> 10:06.250
persecutor of Christians, and he made him alive in Christ.

10:08.052 --> 10:12.377
Paul could sing, if the word's been written, amazing grace.

10:13.258 --> 10:16.141
How sweet the sound that saved a wretch like me.

10:16.201 --> 10:19.865
I once was lost, but now I'm found was blind.

10:20.686 --> 10:21.787
But now I see.

10:21.827 --> 10:24.890
That's what God's grace does.

10:24.950 --> 10:26.312
It finds the lost.

10:26.412 --> 10:27.773
It heals the blind.

10:28.314 --> 10:30.576
It pardons the wicked.

10:30.596 --> 10:32.018
It gives life

10:32.866 --> 10:34.207
to the spiritually dead.

10:34.327 --> 10:37.470
And that's what God did for you, dear Christian.

10:39.232 --> 10:43.356
His grace set Jesus to do for you what you couldn't do for yourself.

10:44.557 --> 10:51.304
So Jesus fulfilled the righteous requirements of the law in his perfect life of love and obedience for you.

10:51.364 --> 11:01.874
And Jesus satisfied the just penalties of God's broken laws and he died the death on the cross that we deserve, bearing the wrath of God to divert it away

11:01.986 --> 11:04.509
away from you and he did more.

11:04.549 --> 11:11.498
He rose from the grave and triumph or the evil one and all evil and he brings you with him in his triumph.

11:11.599 --> 11:21.612
God did this for you and God applied this to you, uniting you to Christ.

11:23.234 --> 11:25.397
That's what the Apostle Paul says.

11:25.417 --> 11:29.522
The second lesson is God saves us by God's grace through faith.

11:29.890 --> 11:34.596
You see that language in verse eight, for by grace you have been saved through faith.

11:35.097 --> 11:42.908
Now some of you are glad that I have finally mentioned faith in four sermons on Ephesians two, one to 10.

11:43.629 --> 11:46.793
After all, we've got to believe in Jesus, don't we?

11:46.853 --> 11:50.838
Well, yes indeed we do, and we are called to trust in Him.

11:50.878 --> 11:54.063
We're called to put our faith in Him.

11:55.084 --> 11:56.466
We cannot be saved.

11:57.058 --> 12:02.666
apart from being united to Christ and the bond of our union with Christ is twofold.

12:03.507 --> 12:24.978
The bond of our union with Christ, what binds us to Christ is on the one hand, God the Holy Spirit, who comes wherever he pleases, like the wind that blows wherever it pleases and he comes and he brings life and he gives a new heart and he awakens and he gives us eyes to see the kingdom and the king and

12:25.218 --> 12:44.864
And with that new heart, that new heart is a heart that is no longer cold-hearted, hard-hearted, in such a way that it refuses to believe, but it's a heart that believes, a heart that trusts in Jesus.

12:46.346 --> 12:52.754
But notice here how comparatively little the apostle says about faith in Jesus.

12:53.602 --> 12:56.886
It's just a passing comment, really, a quick phrase.

12:57.527 --> 13:04.677
You've been saved by grace through faith, and this is not of yourselves, he goes on to say in the very next breath, it's the gift of God.

13:05.999 --> 13:16.032
Paul doesn't have much here to say about faith, not because faith isn't important, but because this passage isn't calling us to faith.

13:17.554 --> 13:23.602
This passage is actually explaining to us why it is we have faith.

13:25.026 --> 13:26.488
God gave His Son for you.

13:27.089 --> 13:28.411
God gave you spiritual life.

13:28.491 --> 13:30.674
God saved you and God graced you.

13:33.298 --> 13:50.683
This is so life-giving to see because it's a temptation for all of us as Christians to misplace our confidence by putting our confidence in our faith instead of putting our confidence in Christ who saves.

13:51.784 --> 13:52.946
When haven't you done this?

13:53.602 --> 13:56.427
I do this again and again, I'm always tempted to do this.

13:59.251 --> 14:00.413
Maybe this is your situation.

14:00.633 --> 14:05.221
You look back and you remember the time when you think you first believed.

14:05.281 --> 14:06.903
Now, some of us don't remember that time.

14:07.184 --> 14:08.866
You don't have to remember that time.

14:09.768 --> 14:13.754
What matters is ultimately not when did you first believe, but do you believe in Jesus now?

14:14.596 --> 14:21.106
But some of us look back at that time and we ask ourselves questions like, back then, did I believe enough?

14:21.858 --> 14:23.560
Was I sincere enough?

14:24.441 --> 14:26.444
Did I get my faith right?

14:28.186 --> 14:40.481
And it can really shake your assurance that God has indeed saved you, been merciful to you and loved you, because you see so much weakness in yourself and in your faith.

14:41.883 --> 14:50.834
But these are not the questions we're being invited to ask, as if our assurance of being saved is bound in what we did for Jesus.

14:51.362 --> 14:55.246
rather than what he did for us.

14:58.189 --> 15:08.199
And the friend who illustrates it this way, if a sick patient gets tuberculosis and the doctor gives them a prescription for penicillin, what will happen if they take it?

15:09.800 --> 15:11.262
They'll die of tuberculosis.

15:11.762 --> 15:12.022
Why?

15:12.543 --> 15:16.907
Because penicillin isn't the antibiotic that treats tuberculosis.

15:17.508 --> 15:19.890
Streptomycin is, and since

15:20.194 --> 15:22.716
those days, other kinds of things I can't even pronounce.

15:23.637 --> 15:24.678
But the point is this.

15:25.920 --> 15:28.722
Faith is only as good as its object.

15:29.863 --> 15:34.668
The act of taking something like medicine is like faith.

15:35.889 --> 15:42.296
You can't take the wrong thing or trust in the wrong thing and get what you need.

15:42.356 --> 15:44.978
Faith isn't the medicine.

15:46.180 --> 15:48.722
Christ is the medicine.

15:49.922 --> 15:53.567
The important thing is to look to Christ and away from yourself.

15:54.749 --> 15:55.891
What a relief that is.

15:57.313 --> 16:00.978
Even weak faith in Christ is saving faith.

16:02.361 --> 16:08.530
The sureness of salvation is in the person and work of Christ, not the strength of our faith in Him.

16:09.952 --> 16:13.838
What a weak faith lays hold of an infinitely strong and loving Savior.

16:13.898 --> 16:15.640
We are assured of everlasting life.

16:17.543 --> 16:19.506
Bishop J.C. Ryle put it this way.

16:19.970 --> 16:30.002
There are some in every congregation that hear the gospel who are ready to despair of their own salvation because their strength seems so small.

16:31.404 --> 16:43.158
They are full of fears and despondency because their knowledge and faith and hope and love appears so dwarfish and diminutive.

16:44.480 --> 16:49.746
Let them know that wheat faith gives a person as real and true a saving interest in Christ

16:49.986 --> 16:53.950
as strong faith, though it may not give them the same joy.

16:54.010 --> 16:59.616
There is life in an infant as truly as in a grown man.

17:00.657 --> 17:06.984
There is fire in a spark as truly as in a flaming or a burning flame.

17:08.165 --> 17:13.991
The least degree of God's grace is an everlasting possession.

17:14.111 --> 17:15.633
It comes down from heaven.

17:16.013 --> 17:17.074
It is precious

17:17.314 --> 17:20.399
in our Lord's eyes and it shall never be overthrown."

17:23.303 --> 17:25.366
So Paul speaks of faith.

17:26.928 --> 17:28.591
What is Christian faith then?

17:28.611 --> 17:35.280
It is receiving and resting upon Christ alone for your salvation.

17:36.562 --> 17:44.594
It's not like skiing up a mountainside from bottom to top in snow.

17:45.474 --> 17:47.336
That would be a difficult chore.

17:48.357 --> 17:50.600
That would be quite a lot of work.

17:51.601 --> 17:56.367
And I suppose we would rightly applaud you if you could even accomplish such a thing.

17:58.048 --> 18:06.959
But the rest of us are going to sit down on a chairlift that takes us from the bottom to the top.

18:07.900 --> 18:13.266
Faith is sitting down on the only thing that can get you from the bottom to the top, so to speak.

18:13.826 --> 18:18.453
The only thing that can get you out of hell and into heaven.

18:20.056 --> 18:22.920
The only thing that can get you for God and God for you.

18:22.960 --> 18:28.609
It's receiving and resting on the only adequate means.

18:30.031 --> 18:34.779
It's receiving and resting on Jesus Christ alone for your salvation.

18:37.182 --> 18:42.130
And so your salvation is not something you have attained by doing.

18:43.202 --> 18:46.728
It is something you have received by believing.

18:46.848 --> 18:52.877
So we sing with Augustus' top lady, not the labors of my hands could fulfill thy laws demands.

18:53.819 --> 18:55.942
Could my zeal no respite know?

18:56.883 --> 18:58.987
Could my tears forever flow?

18:59.047 --> 19:01.370
Could my tears of repentance forever flow?

19:02.532 --> 19:05.236
All for sin could not atone.

19:05.297 --> 19:09.103
Thou must save and thou alone.

19:09.603 --> 19:11.346
Nothing in my hand I bring.

19:11.810 --> 19:13.813
simply to thy cross-eye cling.

19:13.893 --> 19:20.402
Naked come to thee for dress, helpless, look to thee for grace, foul, eye to the fountainfly.

19:21.103 --> 19:24.688
Wash me, Savior, or I die."

19:27.513 --> 19:28.514
Well, here's the third lesson.

19:29.355 --> 19:36.946
God saves us by His grace through faith in Christ as a gift.

19:37.474 --> 19:40.978
We notice that language again, verse 8, for by grace you've been saved through faith.

19:41.258 --> 19:43.080
This not your own doing.

19:43.160 --> 19:49.488
It is the gift of God, not a result of work so that no one can boast.

19:49.508 --> 19:51.670
Salvation is not a work we accomplish.

19:51.790 --> 19:53.212
It is a gift we receive.

19:54.513 --> 20:02.963
Faith is not our contribution to some hypothetically insufficient work.

20:03.684 --> 20:05.746
The work of Christ is not insufficient.

20:06.946 --> 20:15.655
And to mix up faith with works or to mix up faith and works or to call faith a work is to undercut our assurance of salvation.

20:15.715 --> 20:22.683
If we're ever going to be fully confident of anything, we've got to be confident that everything necessary is done.

20:22.723 --> 20:26.126
Not by us, but by him.

20:26.146 --> 20:33.234
And if we think we've contributed just a little bit to our own salvation,

20:34.306 --> 20:36.950
Could our salvation ever be sure and certain?

20:36.970 --> 20:41.198
I mean, aren't you just a little suspicious of yourself?

20:41.738 --> 20:43.982
Don't you find that you have a finical?

20:46.526 --> 20:47.809
Yeah, that's the right word.

20:49.752 --> 20:58.226
Finical, unfaithful, I believe, oh, help my unbelief, kind of heart.

20:59.810 --> 21:04.737
But you know, John, the apostle says in 1 John 4 18, perfect love casts out fear.

21:05.959 --> 21:07.962
And I didn't understand this for a long time.

21:08.203 --> 21:21.943
I thought he was saying that if I had perfect love for Jesus, it would cast out my fears that I wasn't saved or wouldn't fully finally be saved, that I could lose my salvation.

21:21.963 --> 21:23.205
That's not what he's saying at all.

21:24.347 --> 21:29.074
It's the perfect love of God for us that drives out

21:29.378 --> 21:33.885
our fears because it's his gift.

21:33.945 --> 21:58.002
I can have assurance and because it's his gift, I can, I can begin to truly praise him and thank him without in the back of my mind, kneeling before him and imagining in any way, shape or form that I contributed to my salvation and therefore saying, thank you, Lord, that I have me to thank.

22:00.578 --> 22:01.299
That's absurd.

22:01.359 --> 22:03.080
And no Christian does that, of course.

22:03.141 --> 22:09.367
We're saying in our prayer life, even if we get up from prayer and start talking nonsense.

22:11.749 --> 22:16.994
So then faith isn't a good work I do to substitute for the fact that I don't have good works.

22:18.055 --> 22:21.939
This is a false gospel that has been propagated historically.

22:21.979 --> 22:29.266
It's the view that what God requires of humanity is perfect obedience.

22:30.594 --> 22:32.657
But he knows of course that we haven't given it.

22:32.757 --> 22:35.060
So he's lowered the bar of salvation.

22:35.421 --> 22:40.588
And now what he requires instead of perfect loving obedience is faith.

22:41.049 --> 22:51.303
And faith there is viewed as the substitute God receives and welcomes instead of perfect obedience.

22:51.323 --> 22:52.545
That's not what faith is.

22:53.767 --> 22:58.994
Faith is looking away from my works and resting on the finished work of Christ.

23:00.386 --> 23:05.592
Now I know that some of you know that there's been a long debate in Christian theology and scripture interpretation about this passage.

23:06.073 --> 23:16.265
When the Apostle Paul says, and this, not your own doing, it's the gift of God, the question is raised in the scholarly literature.

23:16.325 --> 23:20.750
What is the this that he's referring to?

23:21.150 --> 23:22.772
And I just want to comment on it briefly.

23:22.832 --> 23:24.274
Many have said that the this,

23:24.450 --> 23:28.896
refers to the nearest noun in the sentence, the closest one, and that's faith.

23:28.976 --> 23:32.682
And so he's saying, see, faith is a gift.

23:34.144 --> 23:39.151
Others have said, no, no, because, now listen, if you don't like grammar, just tune out for a second and come back later.

23:39.191 --> 23:43.858
But in Greek, there are masculine and feminine and neuter nouns.

23:44.098 --> 23:49.746
And the issue here is that this, the this is neuter, and all the nouns are feminine,

23:50.050 --> 23:54.956
And normally the this would be the same gender as the noun it's referring to.

23:55.016 --> 24:04.007
So they'll say the this, which is neuter, refers not to any one specific noun in the phrase, but to the whole of the phrase taken together.

24:06.010 --> 24:10.515
The notion of salvation is by grace through faith as a gift.

24:10.655 --> 24:12.398
This is the gift of God.

24:13.839 --> 24:15.341
Well, it certainly is the gift of God.

24:17.123 --> 24:19.186
And as the rest of the Bible makes clear,

24:19.842 --> 24:24.329
faith being part of that is also itself the gift of God.

24:24.369 --> 24:44.498
I mean, if you'll just scan your eyes over at Ephesians 6 verse 23 for a moment, Paul in giving his benediction says, peace be to the brothers or brothers and sisters and love with faith from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.

24:44.962 --> 24:50.731
He's praying that they would have peace, love, and faith, and where would they get it?

24:51.292 --> 24:55.959
They get it from God the Father and the Lord Jesus Christ because it's His gift.

24:55.979 --> 25:02.008
Or consider in Acts chapter 18 the story of Apollos, the Jewish man who was an eloquent teacher.

25:02.068 --> 25:03.710
He'd been instructed in the scriptures.

25:04.091 --> 25:11.602
He actually believed in Jesus, but he was a little deficient in certain things and along came Priscilla and Aquila.

25:11.682 --> 25:17.768
and they instructed him more sufficiently such that he was able eventually to become a help to other believers.

25:17.848 --> 25:31.141
And it says of him in Acts 18 verse 27, having now been instructed properly, he greatly helped those who through grace believed.

25:32.142 --> 25:41.010
It was through grace, God's unmerited favor in the face of their demerits, that they believed.

25:41.762 --> 25:42.723
because it's a gift.

25:43.724 --> 25:48.108
This was Lydia's experience in Acts chapter 16 verse 14.

25:48.209 --> 25:53.294
Lydia, that dear godly woman from Thyatira, a seller of purple goods.

25:53.334 --> 25:59.040
She was a God worshipper and she was down by the river, worshipping God among others.

25:59.360 --> 26:04.845
And yet she hadn't heard of Jesus yet and the Apostle Paul went down there looking for people to preach to.

26:04.946 --> 26:09.330
And it says, the Lord opened her heart

26:10.306 --> 26:14.991
to pay attention to what was said by Paul.

26:16.412 --> 26:24.059
Her heart was closed until the Lord opened it and she paid attention and then she bore the fruit of genuine faith.

26:24.139 --> 26:29.164
She invited them home, fathom and all sorts of things, showed them hospitality.

26:29.665 --> 26:35.791
So that we can say this, the sign on the outside of the door of salvation says what?

26:36.391 --> 26:39.314
It says what Jesus says, there are different ways to put it,

26:39.682 --> 26:46.994
Come to me, all you who are weary and heavy laden, then I will give you rest for your souls.

26:48.135 --> 26:48.796
Come to me.

26:50.138 --> 26:58.171
And you walk through that door coming to Jesus and the door closes behind you, it closes securely, it encloses you in safely.

26:58.892 --> 27:01.456
And you're in Jesus and you're saved.

27:01.576 --> 27:07.666
And you look back at the door and the sign of the door from the backside says, I am the good shepherd.

27:08.258 --> 27:12.142
And I know my own and my own know me, and I give them eternal life.

27:12.202 --> 27:18.828
You did not choose me, but I chose you and appointed you to go and bear fruit."

27:20.590 --> 27:24.714
Why does God save us by grace through faith as a gift and not as a result of works?

27:25.635 --> 27:29.378
Notice, end of verse 9, so that no one can boast.

27:30.900 --> 27:37.266
All boasting in heaven is boasting about the Lamb of God who was slain.

27:37.954 --> 27:39.656
for His people's salvation.

27:41.198 --> 27:46.465
All our boasting on earth should match the boasting of heaven.

27:48.948 --> 27:49.649
You can't earn it.

27:50.690 --> 27:51.511
You can't buy it.

27:52.452 --> 27:53.353
You can't merit it.

27:54.234 --> 27:56.037
You can't make yourself worthy of it.

27:57.258 --> 27:59.842
God must save you or you can't be saved.

28:00.703 --> 28:03.586
God must do it or it will not be done.

28:04.848 --> 28:06.610
And God does these things.

28:07.554 --> 28:11.398
By grace through faith as a gift he saves.

28:12.599 --> 28:14.482
And so then what's the place of good works?

28:16.644 --> 28:18.466
Does it matter if I do anything?

28:19.107 --> 28:21.329
Does it matter how I live at all?

28:22.070 --> 28:23.571
No, no, look at the language.

28:23.591 --> 28:26.635
Verse 10, God saves us by grace through faith and for good works.

28:26.975 --> 28:28.777
For we are his workmanship.

28:29.998 --> 28:36.946
Created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand that we should walk in them.

28:37.826 --> 28:40.389
So Paul is saying, you're not saved by your good works.

28:40.789 --> 28:44.053
You're saved for good works.

28:46.656 --> 28:54.585
As William Temple put it, the only thing of my very own which I contribute to my redemption is the sin from which I need to be redeemed.

28:56.187 --> 29:00.131
And having been redeemed, the apostle says, we are what?

29:01.072 --> 29:04.616
We are His workmanship.

29:04.957 --> 29:06.098
In fact, that's the

29:06.530 --> 29:13.941
the way the language reads, the pronoun his is first, his workmanship, we are.

29:15.243 --> 29:21.933
To emphasize this, it's not by our works, his workmanship, we are.

29:21.953 --> 29:26.320
And the word used is poem, it's the word from which we get the word poem.

29:26.901 --> 29:33.170
You're the poem of God, the creation of God, the artistry of God, the workmanship of God.

29:33.986 --> 29:37.089
You aren't your own creator and you aren't your own savior.

29:39.391 --> 29:40.612
So we might say it this way.

29:40.652 --> 29:47.058
When you find a turtle on the top of a fence post, you know it didn't get there by itself.

29:49.801 --> 29:51.723
How did you get where you are?

29:51.763 --> 29:52.363
Christian.

29:53.644 --> 29:54.225
He worked.

29:55.706 --> 29:56.387
He worked.

29:57.748 --> 30:00.751
Then we were.

30:01.832 --> 30:02.613
We work it out.

30:02.893 --> 30:03.794
We live it out.

30:04.002 --> 30:04.823
We express it.

30:04.884 --> 30:06.507
What kind of works is he talking about?

30:06.527 --> 30:09.452
The good works, which God has pre-planned for us.

30:09.512 --> 30:10.273
Did you see that?

30:10.333 --> 30:10.854
What are those?

30:11.335 --> 30:12.638
Well, he doesn't actually tell us here.

30:13.659 --> 30:14.641
He doesn't spell it out to me.

30:15.062 --> 30:19.089
Verse 11 doesn't tell you the good works that God is interested in seeing you do.

30:19.871 --> 30:25.040
But it would be surprising if he didn't say anything about these good works over the course of the rest of the book.

30:25.060 --> 30:28.306
In fact, chapters 4, 5, and 6 speak of them.

30:29.186 --> 30:35.575
Chapter 4, verse 1, urges us to walk in a manner worthy of the calling to which we have been called.

30:37.057 --> 30:47.611
Chapter 5, verse 1 and 2 says, therefore be imitators of God as beloved children and walk in love as Christ loved us.

30:49.053 --> 30:56.082
And when he starts talking about walking in love, it's interesting how much he simply turns to our various relationships.

30:56.930 --> 31:00.253
I mean, how do you live in the church together with people?

31:01.635 --> 31:06.300
You may have nothing else in common with but Christ.

31:07.301 --> 31:10.524
And you may not even like them, or they may not like you.

31:12.706 --> 31:17.591
Or how do you get along in a marriage that's old and stale?

31:18.312 --> 31:24.498
Or how do parents and children get along with one another when we're tempted to be at each other's throats?

31:25.314 --> 31:26.976
Or how do we relate to unbelievers?

31:27.057 --> 31:31.463
Or how do we deal with spiritual warfare against spiritual entities?

31:31.944 --> 31:33.025
How do we do any of this?

31:33.746 --> 31:34.267
We walk.

31:35.249 --> 31:40.356
Walk, he says, as dearly loved children because Christ loved you.

31:40.436 --> 31:49.069
Walk in love towards others because you're His artwork and He's making you perfectly like Himself.

31:52.634 --> 31:55.218
That perfection to be found, of course, ultimately.

31:55.426 --> 31:56.087
in glory.

31:56.107 --> 31:59.791
But notice then, as we close, how all of this is very humbling.

32:01.873 --> 32:03.014
We didn't save ourselves.

32:03.074 --> 32:05.177
We're saved by His grace, not by our own works.

32:06.298 --> 32:07.559
Even faith is a gift.

32:09.882 --> 32:14.186
And these good works we walk in, He says, God prepared them beforehand.

32:14.907 --> 32:15.568
He planned them.

32:16.369 --> 32:18.711
And then He gave us life and empowers us to do them.

32:19.812 --> 32:24.978
So this isn't, I walked on the moon kind of stuff.

32:25.474 --> 32:33.726
The fans of the comedy bit by Brian Regan will know that he tells it better than the non-comedian before you.

32:33.826 --> 32:41.717
But he says, would you imagine for a moment being at a dinner party where someone is there called the Me Monster?

32:42.959 --> 32:45.563
Someone who's always talking about me.

32:45.603 --> 32:47.165
I did this.

32:47.185 --> 32:48.187
I did that.

32:48.487 --> 32:49.168
I own this.

32:49.408 --> 32:50.570
I own that.

32:50.650 --> 32:52.573
The Me Monster, me, me, me, me, me.

32:52.593 --> 32:53.394
That's Brian Regan.

32:53.890 --> 32:56.715
Regan imagines Neil Armstrong at that party.

32:57.776 --> 33:04.788
Just eating his food, sipping his soup, biting his time while the me monster talks on and on.

33:04.908 --> 33:12.781
And finally, Neil Armstrong looks up and says, oh yeah, I walked on the moon.

33:14.805 --> 33:15.886
Conversation ended.

33:17.168 --> 33:18.130
What could top that?

33:20.258 --> 33:32.717
Well, Paul isn't telling you that you're alive in Christ, raised with Christ, seated with Christ in heavenly places, and therefore God's workmanship so that you can say, oh, yeah?

33:34.560 --> 33:35.061
Look at me.

33:35.081 --> 33:39.507
No, it's for by grace you have been saved through faith.

33:40.489 --> 33:41.911
And this is not your own doing.

33:42.873 --> 33:49.042
It's the gift of God, not as a result of work so that no one can boast.

33:50.402 --> 33:55.187
Let me call you, dear Christian, to boast in the Lord.

33:55.848 --> 33:56.369
Let's pray.

33:58.871 --> 34:09.123
We do, we would give you all honor and praise and glory and freely acknowledge that we were helpless when you helped us.

34:11.485 --> 34:16.551
It was worse than we knew that salvation is better than we could have ever guessed.

34:18.293 --> 34:19.474
Grant us to know

34:20.290 --> 34:23.798
How wide and long and deep and high is this love of Christ for us?

34:23.898 --> 34:25.081
In Jesus' name we pray.

34:26.124 --> 34:26.504
Amen.

34:27.366 --> 34:27.627
Amen.

34:27.667 --> 34:32.338
Let's stand together and sing.

